      void evalEachLn(java.lang.String buf)
      evaluates the postfix notation string passed into it, buf turns buf into a character array, and loops through the array to look at the characters if the character is a number, it is pushed onto the stack if the character is a operator, it operates it on the last two numbers in the stack, then pushes the new value onto the stack once it is done evaluating, the last number on the stack is the answer, and is popped prints the final answer
